task.summary: Default task
Some markdown.
Upgraded to ST 2.2.1 (using the latest cmd line tool).
LnF slightly improved (still far away from being responsive) nicer menu icon shades removed on detail lots of stuff added to detail
icons for android LnF improved

switching back to Ext.util.Geolocation due to non-working Ext.device.Geolocation on android (see also http://www.sencha.com/forum/showthread.php?214165-No-Response-from-Ext.device.Geolocation.getCurrentPosition()-on-Android.&p=975083)
Removed connections-to-stations.txt.
Switched to Meteotest data model. Fixes #24.
Fixed geolocation lookup.
Removed debugger statement.
Removed debugger statement.
The current location now has a 'closestPublicTransportStation{name,id}'. Only the IDs are used from now on to access transport API. Fixes #28.
Parse forecast data and add it to Station model. Fixes #29.
Fixed to NPEs.
Switched from model.data.attribute to model.get('attribute') consequently.
Replaced invalid chars.
Switched to awk-based solution to transform wmo2sbb.md. Update for #26.
Preparation for #32.
More preparations for #32.
"Officially" added arrival/departure to model.
Switched back to live data.
Fixed inconsistency with the temperatur attributes. It's 'tt10' in the current data but 'tt' in the forecast.
Added forecast to detail view. Fixes #32.
Addendum to #32, forecast data also needs to be parsed with custom method (Safari complained).
Added explanation for index.php.
Applied JSON formatting (i.e. pretty-printing).
Replace 'now' on detail screen. Fixes #35.
Interpret Meteotest time stamps as UTC. Fixes #36.
Changed mapping of sunshine minutes to sun level. Fixes #34.
Added variations of the shades image (for what it's worth).
Produced and re-organized all app icons (all variations included).
Changed mapping of sunshine minutes to sun level. Fixes #34.
Fixed the only four iOS icons currently supported by Sencha native build (icons must not have transparent background).
Fixed the only four iOS icons currently supported by Sencha native build (icons must not have transparent background).
Added Android/iOS packager configs.
First small step towards a full implementation of the filtering algorithm #3. Filter shouldn't hang indefinitely anymore.
Finally switching to Ext.device.Geolocation (leaving the other alternatives commented out).
